You are given the root of a binary search tree (BST), where the values of exactly two nodes of the tree were swapped by mistake. Recover the tree without changing its structure.

 

Example 1:
Input: root = [1,3,null,null,2]
Output: [3,1,null,null,2]
Explanation: 3 cannot be a left child of 1 because 3 > 1. Swapping 1 and 3 makes the BST valid.

Example 2:
Input: root = [3,1,4,null,null,2]
Output: [2,1,4,null,null,3]
Explanation: 2 cannot be in the right subtree of 3 because 2 < 3. Swapping 2 and 3 makes the BST valid.






Code
/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * public class TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode left;
 *     TreeNode right;
 *     TreeNode() {}
 *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {
 *         this.val = val;
 *         this.left = left;
 *         this.right = right;
 *     }
 * }
 */
class Solution {
    TreeNode prevNode= null;
    TreeNode galat1First= null;
    TreeNode galat1Second= null;
    TreeNode galat2First= null;
    TreeNode galat2Second= null;
    int galat=0; 
    public void recoverTree(TreeNode root) {
        inOrder(root);
        if(galat==1){
            int temp=galat1First.val;
            galat1First.val=galat1Second.val;
            galat1Second.val=temp;
        }else{
            int temp=galat1First.val;
            galat1First.val=galat2Second.val;
            galat2Second.val=temp;
        }
        return;
    }

    public void inOrder(TreeNode root){
        if(root==null) return;

        inOrder(root.left);
        if(prevNode == null ){
            prevNode=root;
        }else{
            if(root.val<=prevNode.val){
                if(galat==0){
                    galat1First=prevNode;
                    galat1Second=root;
                    galat++;
                }else{
                    galat2First=prevNode;
                    galat2Second=root;
                    galat++;
                }
            }
            prevNode=root;
        }
        inOrder(root.right);
    }
}




